cs.IT, cs.GT, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.DS 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the optimal rate region for source coding and information exchange among users. 
2. cs.GT (Game Theory) is also likely as the paper uses coalitional game theory to study fairness solutions. 
3. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is relevant as the paper proposes network coding schemes to implement the fractional egalitarian solution. 
4. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is relevant as the paper discusses the decomposition of the game into subgames for distributed computation. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is less likely but still possible as the paper proposes a polynomial-time approximation method for the Shapley value.
